---
import Layout from "../layouts/BlogPost.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About Ben Brannen"
  description="Ben Brannen builds practical intelligence tools for automation, market research, dashboards, source-backed systems, and Small Town Capital."
  pubDate={new Date("June 3 2026")}
  heroImage="/atl_thon.jpg"
>
  <style>
    :global(.prose.prose) {
      width: min(920px, calc(100% - 2rem)) !important;
      max-width: calc(100% - 2rem) !important;
      padding-inline: 0 !important;
    }

    :global(.title.title) {
      max-width: 760px !important;
      margin-inline: auto !important;
    }

    .about-kicker {
      color: var(--accent);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .about-lede {
      color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      line-height: 1.55;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .about-card {
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72);
      border: 1px solid rgba(var(--gray), 0.18);
      border-radius: 18px;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 28px rgba(var(--gray), 0.12);
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
      padding: 1.55rem 1.7rem;
    }

    .about-card h2,
    .about-card h3 {
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    .theme-panel {
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
      padding: 1.55rem 1.7rem;
    }

    .theme-panel > p {
      color: rgb(var(--gray));
      margin-top: -0.25rem;
    }

    .theme-list {
      display: grid;
      gap: 1rem;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(245px, 1fr));
      list-style: none;
      margin: 1.25rem 0 0;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .theme-list li {
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.62);
      border: 1px solid rgba(var(--gray), 0.16);
      border-radius: 14px;
      padding: 0.95rem;
    }

    .theme-list strong {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }

    .pill-list {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.55rem;
      list-style: none;
      margin: 1rem 0 0;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .pill-list li {
      background: rgba(55, 80, 92, 0.09);
      border: 1px solid rgba(55, 80, 92, 0.18);
      border-radius: 999px;
      color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      line-height: 1.25;
      padding: 0.45rem 0.72rem;
    }

    .small-note {
      color: rgb(var(--gray));
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .connect-box {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(55, 80, 92, 0.12), rgba(31, 93, 66, 0.12));
      border: 1px solid rgba(55, 80, 92, 0.2);
      border-radius: 20px;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      .about-lede {
        font-size: 1.12rem;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <p class="about-kicker">Builder · Investigator · Operator</p>

  <p class="about-lede">
    I’m Ben. I build practical tools around messy systems: dashboards,
    automations, market notes, source-backed research, and small experiments that
    turn confusion into something useful.
  </p>

  <div class="about-card">
    <h2>What I’m building now</h2>
    <p>
      My current work is centered around <strong>Small Town Capital</strong>: a
      research-driven operating identity for market speculation, local
      intelligence, automation, public writing, and eventually real-world capital
      allocation.
    </p>
    <p>
      The public version is not a guru page or a victory-lap feed. It is an
      operator journal: what I’m seeing, what I’m building, what I’m learning,
      and where the process still needs work.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="about-card theme-panel">
    <h2>Systems and project themes</h2>
    <p>
      The common thread is turning scattered information into cleaner decisions,
      repeatable workflows, and a public trail of the work.
    </p>
    <ul class="theme-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Research dashboards</strong>
        Turning notes, data, filings, and watchlists into decision systems.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Automation workflows</strong>
        Using scripts, APIs, spreadsheets, and agents to remove repetitive work.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Source-backed research</strong>
        Keeping claims tied to original sources, context, and open questions.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Trading Command Center</strong>
        A private dashboard for market research, options structures, decision
        logs, and review discipline.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Options Council</strong>
        An agent-style framework for debating convexity, theta, risk, tactics,
        and final trade verdicts.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Operator journal</strong>
        Writing publicly about the process without pretending every idea is
        already polished.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <div class="about-card">
    <h2>How I think about the work</h2>
    <p>
      The loop is simple:
      <strong>research → structure → publish → build → invest → learn → repeat.</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      I’m interested in overlooked markets, overlooked towns, overlooked data,
      and overlooked workflows. The goal is to build machines that remember the
      thesis better than my emotions do.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="about-card">
    <h2>Tools and background</h2>
    <p>
      I studied finance at Georgia Southern University and have spent years
      working across spreadsheets, data visualization, automation, scripting,
      and practical problem solving.
    </p>
    <ul class="pill-list" aria-label="Technical skills and tools">
      <li>Google Sheets</li>
      <li>Excel</li>
      <li>Apps Script</li>
      <li>Python</li>
      <li>SQL</li>
      <li>Bash / Linux</li>
      <li>Looker Studio</li>
      <li>Power BI</li>
      <li>Astro</li>
      <li>HTML / CSS / JavaScript</li>
      <li>Raspberry Pi</li>
      <li>Google Cloud Certified Digital Leader</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="about-card">
    <h2>Outside the terminal</h2>
    <p>
      I’m also a runner, skier, self-directed guitar player, and someone who has
      learned a lot from turning personal challenges into data projects.
    </p>
    <p>
      One example: I once ran <a href="https://lookerstudio.google.com/u/0/reporting/29998d2b-7d6e-4f42-b4e7-cfa489bff4a9/page/tlXZD">102 straight days of 5K+</a>
      and turned the streak into a dashboard. That is basically the theme here:
      do the thing, instrument the thing, learn from the thing.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="connect-box">
    <h2>Let’s connect</h2>
    <p>
      If you’re interested in dashboards, automation, source-backed research,
      market structure, Small Town Capital, or weird useful systems, reach out.
    </p>
    <p>
      Email: <a href="mailto:benjamin.m.brannen@gmail.com">benjamin.m.brannen@gmail.com</a><br />
      LinkedIn: <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/benjamin-brannen">linkedin.com/in/benjamin-brannen</a>
    </p>
    <p class="small-note">
      Nothing here is investment advice. This site is a public notebook for
      projects, experiments, research habits, and lessons learned while building.
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>
